FIVE THINGS TO DO IN NEW YORK that are not eating or drinking (winter edition) 
1. Go to the Rockettes at Radio City Music Hall. I was truly amazed at how in sync the dancers were. It was a great show. 
2. Get the viral $40 blowout in Chinatown. No joke my hair has never felt cleaner, they shampoo your hair twice and give you a shoulder massage. I highly recommend!! 
3. Another great option would be to go ice-skating at The Rink at the Rockefeller Center. The tree will be lit December 3 this year!! Definitely a cool experience, especially if you love the movie Elf. 
4. Check out the viral Old Friend Photo Booth, which is at 117 Orchard St. These photos come out so cute, they are black and white definitely a vibe. Iâ€™m pretty sure they were seven dollars for two. 
5. Go to the holiday pop-up on 5th Ave. So many different stores had booths here with holiday gifts, merchandise, snacks, viral foods, hot chocolates they even had ice-skating!

Have fun!!
